The paper presents a novel mapping framework for robot navigation, which suggests that it falls under the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The framework involves 3D voxel grids and 2D occupancy grids, which are commonly used in Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions real-time erosion and re-integration of measurements, which involves optimization and control, indicating that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
